                    <comment id="12867126" author="ab" created="Thu, 13 May 2010 13:50:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Modified unit test to illustrate the problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12867130" author="ab" created="Thu, 13 May 2010 14:30:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The test passes with this patch. I&apos;m not completely sure it coveres all cases, though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12867165" author="mikemccand" created="Thu, 13 May 2010 17:17:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Andrzej &amp;#8211; this is indeed a bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Your fix (using flex API on pre-flex API emulation) is good for now, so I think we can commit to trunk.  But, we are going to remove the pre-flex APIs (and make the flex APIs abstract) soonish, at which point all FilterIndexReader impls for trunk will have to cutover to flex.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll commit shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
